title: Winter Squash Muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first six ingredients. In a small bowl, whisk the egg, squash, buttermilk, honey and butter. Stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened.

Coat muffin cups with cooking spray or use paper liners; fill half full. Bake at 350Â° for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack. Yield: 1 dozen.
